description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you love working with patients who have a neurological condition and are up for an exciting working opportunity? Do you see yourself as a team player who advocates for the patient and the profession? If the answer is yes then we have the role for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, highly motivated, innovative and friendly Occupational Therapist to join our team of therapists at The Shrewsbury and Telford Hospital NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is based at The Royal Shrewsbury Hospital which is a major trauma unit and receives patients for ongoing rehabilitation from the major trauma centre at Stoke, as well as patients who do not need trauma centre care who present with neurological deficit following an acquired brain injury or stroke. This post is the lead therapist within their profession for neurological conditions for patients admitted to the hospital, also to support the Occupational Therapy team in the acute setting, supporting patients across many ward areas and clinical specialities as well as being the clinical resource for training and development of the general medical, surgical and orthopaedic teams. Our acute stroke service is based at Telford. This role is also expected to deliver sessions to both neurological outpatients and early supported stroke service (ESD).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your week would be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 sessions on the acute wards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 sessions in ESD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 sessions in outpatients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has a background in neurological conditions at band 6 or band 7 level who has experience of training and education of clinicians supporting patients rehabilitation and discharge planning. You will ideally be a clinical educator and have experience of delivering supervision of staff within a team. You will be required to undertake and/ or support one piece of audit per year relevant to your clinical area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Shrewsbury and Telford Hospital NHS Trust has been in the national media over recent years for a variety of issues and we are committed to change for patient and staff benefit. Within therapies we have a strong culture of professional leadership and support within each profession having a head of profession leading on delivering local, regional and national professional strategy. This includes but is not exhaustive of AHP’s into action, job planning, electronic rostering, electronic data capture, quality improvement strategy, and representation at internal and external meetings raising the profile of therapies at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Trust Shrewsbury and Telford Hospital have for the last 5 years been advantaged by being linked with the Virginia Mason Institute in Seattle, USA. This affiliation has seen the implementation of improvement tools focusing on the patient at the centre across the organisation with Therapies being trained in Lean methodologies at not only lean for leaders and also advanced lean training levels. We are proud to have a culture of patient focused care utilising our resourced to the best of our abilities. You will have the opportunity to be training in lean methodology and supporting in service review and improvement supported by dedicated therapy quality improvement leads and management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our patient centred care we require all staff to support our weekend working rota and therefore this role will be required to work across a 7 day working pattern .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to meeting you at interview and exploring all the opportunities you will gain by joining us in this exciting and essential role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
